  <span id="freeText14539065442452432670" style="display:none">One thing that lacks in the front cover or what this novel recommends before reading it is the note: YOU MUST BE A JAMES DEAN FAN! Guevara ventures on putting out a story written for the general adult audience and gambles on "You don't need to know my characters beforehand. Just enjoy my narrative."<br /><br />Bold aim. To me, I pretended not to know James Dean and still had a joyous ride in what a novel puts you through, in reading Lips of a Mastodon. But that's me, a Hollywood flake.<br /><br />Furthermore, Guevara writes a nihilistic bent novel, in the tradition of Brett Easton Ellis and Palahniuk. The odds became higher. <br /><br />My urge to read just doubled.</span>
